WEBVTT

00:04.333 --> 00:06.000
<i>Previously on St. Elsewhere.</i>

00:06.067 --> 00:08.202
What happened to these guys?
Street Fight.

00:08.269 --> 00:10.571
Some paddies jumped us.
I love urban Living.

00:10.638 --> 00:15.610
- Why, you--
- You got beat up
by some negroes.

00:15.676 --> 00:18.412
Listen, did you get your stuff
moved into my apartment?

00:18.479 --> 00:20.848
Yeah. I just gotta
move Morrison's Couch.

00:20.915 --> 00:23.150
She's barely
out of nursing school.

00:23.217 --> 00:25.152
He's working his way
through the building.

00:25.219 --> 00:26.954
My old man hasn't worked
since June.

00:27.021 --> 00:30.324
Can't get work out there anyway,
not unless your skin's
the color of Coal.

00:30.391 --> 00:32.326
<i>Tonight on st. Elsewhere.</i>

00:32.393 --> 00:34.996
Dr. Cavanero, I see you're
working the halls
like everyone else.

00:35.062 --> 00:37.398
Did you get the invite
to my party for sven holstrum?

00:37.465 --> 00:40.534
- Yes, I did,
but I can't make it.
- This is not a stag party.

00:40.601 --> 00:43.471
Get a date.
And while you're at it,
get a haircut.

00:45.373 --> 00:47.308
The rest of the sorority?

00:47.375 --> 00:49.977
Peter, I'm pregnant.
What?

00:50.044 --> 00:51.946
[ Clears Throat ]

00:52.013 --> 00:53.948
is something wrong?
No, Nothing's wrong.

00:54.015 --> 00:57.618
<i>Valkommen, valkommen,
 valkommen.</i>

00:57.685 --> 01:01.956
So I said to Borg-- I said,
"bjorn, use your backstroke."
Ooh, I'm sorry.

01:02.023 --> 01:04.724
Oh, what have I done?

01:04.792 --> 01:07.561
What's he doing in here?
He's a patient.

01:07.628 --> 01:10.031
What does it look like?
I don't want him in
the same room with my son.

01:10.097 --> 01:12.166
I learned to fight
the same place you did,
pally-Boy.

01:12.233 --> 01:14.368
There's nothing I'd
like better right now
than to tear you apart.

03:09.250 --> 03:11.385
<i>[ woman on P.A. ]
Dr. Siler to maternity.</i>

03:11.452 --> 03:14.922
<i>Dr. Paul Siler to maternity.</i>

03:20.461 --> 03:23.798
<i>[ grunting, shouting ]</i>

03:23.864 --> 03:27.668
<i>[ man ]
Hey!
[ Chattering ]</i>

03:27.735 --> 03:30.638
<i>security!</i>

03:32.740 --> 03:35.042
[ Shouting CONTINUES ]

03:35.109 --> 03:38.512
<i>[ woman ]
call security.
[ man ] break it up!</i>

03:38.579 --> 03:41.115
<i>[ man ]
what's happening out there?</i>

03:41.182 --> 03:44.518
<i>[ woman on P.A. ]
security to 2-West.
Are you okay?</i>

03:44.585 --> 03:47.154
<i>Security to 2-West immediately.</i>

03:47.221 --> 03:49.857
Hey!
All right. We got it.

03:49.924 --> 03:52.893
Come on! Break it up here!
Come on!

03:52.960 --> 03:56.631
[ Shouting ]
Come on!

03:56.697 --> 04:00.034
<i>[ Man ]
his breathing is irregular
at the moment.</i>

04:00.101 --> 04:02.036
They're trying
to stabilize him.

04:02.103 --> 04:06.240
<i>[ woman on P.A. ]
Dr. Helenov to E.R.
Dr. Helenov to E.R.</i>

04:06.307 --> 04:09.477
Send Mr. Masius up to psych.
Beale'll have a field day.

04:10.978 --> 04:13.547
E.T., phone home.

04:13.614 --> 04:15.549
Speaking of home,
have you found a place to live?

04:15.616 --> 04:17.851
No, I'm still with Ehrlich.
How's that going?

04:17.918 --> 04:20.620
Ask Ehrlich.
On second thought, don't.
Who's next?

04:20.688 --> 04:24.225
I saved this one
especially for you.
Her name is Rowena Hampton.

04:24.292 --> 04:27.561
Sharp pain on her right side.
My guess is it's her appendix.

04:27.628 --> 04:29.630
There's only one way
to find out.

04:29.697 --> 04:32.500
Miss Hampton,
I'm Dr. Fiscus.
Hiya, doc.

04:36.237 --> 04:38.973
How are you doing? Okay?

04:43.277 --> 04:46.247
Just a few more steps.

04:46.314 --> 04:49.984
Take off
all your clothes, please.
Oh, anything you say, doc.

04:50.051 --> 04:52.219
Now you know
why I love medicine.

04:58.492 --> 05:00.428
Excuse me.

05:00.494 --> 05:02.430
There's somebody
here to see you.

05:02.496 --> 05:05.566
Who is it?
It's your wife.

05:07.368 --> 05:09.370
I'll-- I'll take over here.

05:09.437 --> 05:11.372
Excuse me.
I'll be right back.

05:11.439 --> 05:13.374
<i>[ woman on P.A. ]
Dr. Arony to I.C.U.</i>

05:13.441 --> 05:16.611
<i>Dr. Daniel arony to I.C.U.</i>

05:19.146 --> 05:21.082
Hey.

05:21.148 --> 05:24.385
What are you doing here?
Look, I really
hate doing this.

05:24.452 --> 05:28.089
This is about money again,
isn't it?
I gotta have $200.

05:28.155 --> 05:30.725
But I don't need it
right away.
Oh, yeah? When?

05:30.791 --> 05:34.562
In about a week, 10 days.
It might just as well
be right now.

05:34.629 --> 05:36.530
What's it for this time,
French Horn lessons?

05:40.668 --> 05:42.637
What does that say?

05:44.071 --> 05:47.308
Fiscus, you're using
a rectal thermometer.
It's clean.

05:47.375 --> 05:50.444
The garage called.
We need a new carburetor.

05:50.511 --> 05:54.448
What are you talking about?
I'm gonna call that mechanic.

05:54.515 --> 05:57.184
No, Peter, don't.
No. I talked to him
last week.

05:57.251 --> 05:59.387
He said everything
with that car was just fine.

05:59.453 --> 06:01.389
[ sighs ]

06:01.455 --> 06:03.424
you're lying to me.

06:05.426 --> 06:08.729
Peter, I'm pregnant.
What?

06:08.796 --> 06:13.034
I'm pregnant.
How can you be so stupid?

06:13.100 --> 06:15.102
We're barely
getting by as it is.

06:15.169 --> 06:20.074
I know.
That's why I want the money,
so that I can get rid of it.

06:20.141 --> 06:23.377
You can do that here.
It won't cost us anything.

06:23.444 --> 06:28.416
Sure. That'd be just terrific.
Then everyone we know
can be talking about it.

06:30.651 --> 06:33.487
It's not mine, is it?
No.

06:33.554 --> 06:35.790
Then you just get
the money from him.

06:44.298 --> 06:46.234
You were right.
It's appendectomy time.

06:46.300 --> 06:48.369
I'll let surgery know.
Who's on call?

06:48.436 --> 06:51.005
Samuels.
What goes around
comes around.

06:51.072 --> 06:53.241
What's that supposed to mean?
Last time he had a Hooker,

06:53.307 --> 06:56.510
he was unconscious
on the Table.

06:59.146 --> 07:01.582
Mr. Masius, someone
from your planet
will be here soon.

07:01.649 --> 07:03.551
Thanks.

07:05.453 --> 07:07.455
What happened?
We made the mistake
of putting a kid...

07:07.521 --> 07:10.191
from canisius high
in the same room with
a kid from Carver.

07:10.258 --> 07:12.193
Oh, boy.
[ sighs ]

07:12.260 --> 07:15.363
I guess we should expect
this kind of trouble with
What's been going on here...

07:15.429 --> 07:17.632
the past couple of days.
How did they end up
in the same room?

07:17.698 --> 07:19.901
Admitting doesn't screen
patients like a dating service.

07:19.967 --> 07:22.603
They just fill the beds.
First come, first served.

07:22.670 --> 07:25.072
They were
going at it pretty good
when security arrived.

07:25.139 --> 07:27.074
That's why I hired
the extra security guards.

07:27.141 --> 07:29.877
What else can we do?
Hand out boxing gloves?

07:29.944 --> 07:32.947
Yeah. Uh, Kevin O'Connor.
Is he back from x-ray?

07:33.014 --> 07:35.416
Yes, he is.
And his remaining kidney
Stabilized.

07:35.483 --> 07:38.252
Terrific. I like that kid.
Oh, Donald.

07:38.319 --> 07:41.188
Mark.
Did you get the invite to my
party for sven holstrum?

07:41.255 --> 07:44.725
Yes, I did, but I can't make it.
It's parents' night
at Elizabeth's school.

07:44.792 --> 07:47.595
Oh, no.
This is important, Donald.

07:47.662 --> 07:50.364
Somebody else
From administration
has to be there.

07:50.431 --> 07:53.367
I can't ask auschlander,
with his chemotherapy
and everything.

07:53.434 --> 07:56.304
Daniel's looking pretty Good.
He's back to work,
and he feels great.

07:56.370 --> 07:59.473
Listen, just drop by
for five minutes
to shake hands with the man.

07:59.540 --> 08:03.177
I can't do it, mark.
Parents' night is once a year.

08:03.244 --> 08:06.013
It's a slap in the face.
Another example
of St. Eligius...

08:06.080 --> 08:08.816
thumbing its nose
to a medical genius.

08:13.054 --> 08:15.356
She doesn't look
like a prostitute.
Come on, V.J.

08:15.423 --> 08:18.292
We're all selling something.
It's a question
of establishing price.

08:18.359 --> 08:21.028
â™ªâ™ª [ Humming ]

08:21.095 --> 08:24.298
will you stop that?
What are you so happy
about today?

08:24.365 --> 08:27.501
You're depressing me.
The grin shows
right through your Mask.

08:27.568 --> 08:30.504
I'm on call.
I'm definitely on call
for the next 48 hours.

08:30.571 --> 08:33.006
You okay?
Suture.
Now I am.

08:33.073 --> 08:36.309
Yesterday I was locked
into attending
Dr. Craig's cocktail party.

08:36.376 --> 08:38.645
<i>What party?
[ V.J. ]
the one he's giving...</i>

08:38.712 --> 08:40.982
<i>in honor of Dr. Sven holstrum,</i>

08:41.048 --> 08:43.317
the noted
scandinavian heart surgeon.

08:43.384 --> 08:45.419
Are you invited too?
Wanna cut that?

08:45.486 --> 08:49.156
Uh, no. I heard it
through the grapevine.

08:49.223 --> 08:53.327
Will you listen to him?
We gotta keep him away
from these '60s soul Tapes.

08:53.394 --> 08:55.529
He thinks he's Gladys Knight.
Clamp it.

08:55.596 --> 08:57.665
Craig didn't invite you, beano?

08:57.732 --> 09:00.635
I'm not surprised.
He can barely deal
with me professionally.

09:00.701 --> 09:03.204
Who knows how he'd react
with a fistful of Aquavit.

09:03.271 --> 09:06.240
- Okay, let's get the appendix.
- Well, anyhoo,

09:06.307 --> 09:08.776
I r.S.V.P.'d,
but I really didn't want to go.

09:08.843 --> 09:11.913
It's taken me three days
of schedule juggling
and collecting I.O.U.'s...

09:11.979 --> 09:14.815
to insure that
I'm definitely on call.

09:14.882 --> 09:17.818
Good work.
You don't want to go?

09:17.885 --> 09:19.887
Are you kidding?
I'm not spending
a rare night off...

09:19.954 --> 09:22.623
trading snappy repartee
with Craig and his friends.

09:22.690 --> 09:25.826
I don't blame you.
But the truth,
you couldn't get a date, right?

09:25.893 --> 09:28.162
No, not a prayer.

09:28.229 --> 09:31.465
Hey, listen, how about--

09:34.702 --> 09:37.038
Mmm. Nice.

09:37.104 --> 09:40.441
[ man on tv ]
the tension continues
in Boston city schools...

09:40.508 --> 09:43.077
in the aftermath of last week's
racial Disturbances.

09:43.144 --> 09:47.748
Jim Dawkins, spokesman for the
school system, said today that
unless cooler heads prevail--

09:47.815 --> 09:49.717
this isn't healthy for you.

09:51.485 --> 09:56.824
<i>Ah, that's better.
So what have you been up to?</i>

09:56.891 --> 09:59.627
[ Groans ]
just thinking.

09:59.694 --> 10:03.264
You in any pain?
Nothing I can't handle.

10:03.331 --> 10:06.400
I just looked over your x-Rays
with Dr. Westphall.

10:06.467 --> 10:08.402
You're not gonna lose
your other kidney.

10:08.469 --> 10:10.504
That means I'm not gonna
get hooked up to any machines?

10:10.571 --> 10:13.841
That's right.
Wow.

10:13.908 --> 10:15.943
Thank you.

10:16.010 --> 10:18.579
Hey, doc,
what happened to him?

10:18.646 --> 10:22.016
<i>Got hit in the head
with a brick.
White guys do it?</i>

10:22.083 --> 10:24.852
Happened in
a white neighborhood.

10:26.020 --> 10:28.089
Looks pretty bad.
Got a concussion.

10:29.557 --> 10:31.492
It's all my fault.

10:31.559 --> 10:33.761
What is?
All this trouble.

10:33.828 --> 10:37.131
I hardly think you can blame
yourself for getting mugged.

10:37.198 --> 10:39.667
But my brother Mike
and his friends
Went after those Guys.

10:39.734 --> 10:41.769
Yeah, I know. We're treating
a lot of 'em here.

10:41.836 --> 10:44.939
But now their friends
want revenge, and the whole
thing's out of control.

10:45.006 --> 10:46.974
You can't worry
about that.

10:48.276 --> 10:50.211
Just concentrate
on getting better.

10:50.278 --> 10:52.813
Okay.

10:52.880 --> 10:55.116
Anything I can get you?

10:55.182 --> 10:57.084
No.

10:58.319 --> 11:01.322
I'll stop by
and see you later.

11:01.389 --> 11:05.826
But his plane will arrive
at Logan at 4:06.

11:05.893 --> 11:08.195
We'll be home by 6:00
at the latest.

11:14.035 --> 11:17.905
Ellen, the traffic problem
is mine, okay?

11:17.972 --> 11:21.842
You just make sure that
the hors D'oeuvres are ready
when we come through the door.

11:21.909 --> 11:24.512
What do you want?
Oh, yeah. Sit down.

11:24.579 --> 11:28.182
Ellen, we'll talk about this
when I get home, okay?

11:29.283 --> 11:31.619
Boy!
[ Chuckles ]

11:31.686 --> 11:33.754
Mrs. Craig's a little nervous...

11:33.821 --> 11:36.557
with All the preparations
for tomorrow night.

11:36.624 --> 11:40.528
Okay, hors d'oeuvres,
car wash--
I told her not to worry.

11:40.595 --> 11:44.665
The key to a good party is
to have the right ambience.
That's what I've always heard.

11:44.732 --> 11:48.402
I mean, we're trying to make
Dr. Holstrum feel at home.

11:48.469 --> 11:52.873
So this time we'll go with
a potpourri of Scandinavia.

11:52.940 --> 11:55.977
Swedish meatballs,
danish pastries--

11:56.043 --> 11:58.613
Norwegian wood.

11:58.679 --> 12:00.615
What do you want, Ehrlich?

12:00.681 --> 12:02.984
Well, sir,
it's about the party.
It's gonna be great.

12:03.050 --> 12:05.219
I know. That's why I'm
sorry I'm gonna miss it.

12:05.286 --> 12:07.622
My wife told me you canceled.
That's a pity.

12:07.688 --> 12:10.291
You know how it is
with first-year residents.

12:10.358 --> 12:13.861
Sure, sure. One minute
you're on, and the next
minute you're off.

12:13.928 --> 12:17.665
<i>Yeah. I'm real sorry
I won't be able to make it.</i>

12:17.732 --> 12:19.734
Well, then, I have
really good news for you.

12:19.800 --> 12:21.769
I'm gonna do a little tinkering
with the schedule...

12:21.836 --> 12:24.038
and make sure you're free
and clear for tomorrow night.

12:24.105 --> 12:26.674
[ chuckles ]
ah.

12:26.741 --> 12:31.345
I, uh-- I don't know
quite what to say, sir.
A simple "Thank you" will do.

12:31.412 --> 12:35.149
Uh, you know, Dr. Craig,
I really hate to
inconvenience anyone else.

12:35.216 --> 12:37.151
Now, listen to me, Ehrlich.

12:37.218 --> 12:40.755
Sven holstrum is world Famous
for his work on
the artificial heart.

12:40.821 --> 12:42.757
It's important for you
to be there.

12:42.823 --> 12:45.893
This is a rare opportunity
for you to meet the man.

12:47.028 --> 12:49.530
You're right.
It's a rare opportunity.

12:49.597 --> 12:52.867
Thank you.
Of course, you'll be bringing
a suitable companion.

12:52.934 --> 12:55.636
- sir?
- A date, Ehrlich.

12:55.703 --> 12:57.872
Preferably somebody
of the female persuasion.

12:57.939 --> 13:00.341
Well, I'm afraid I
don't have much time.

13:00.408 --> 13:04.211
This is not
a stag party, Ehrlich.
Get a date!

13:04.278 --> 13:06.714
And while you're at it,
get a haircut.

13:07.815 --> 13:10.885
Yes, sir.
See you tomorrow night.

13:10.952 --> 13:13.955
6:15.
Sharp.

13:17.758 --> 13:19.660
[ Sighs ]

13:33.941 --> 13:35.943
Hi.
Hi.

13:36.010 --> 13:39.180
You'll be happy to know
the heat's back on in ward 5.

13:39.247 --> 13:41.449
I didn't know it was off.
Mm-Hmm.

13:44.719 --> 13:49.423
Not exactly
the women's auxiliary.
See you tomorrow.

13:49.490 --> 13:52.593
<i>[ people chattering ]</i>

14:01.135 --> 14:03.070
I wish I could go with you.
Like Dad always says,

14:03.137 --> 14:05.239
her cooking's the only thing
worth Getting dressed up for.

14:05.306 --> 14:07.642
I'll call her and tell her
you'll be there next week.

14:07.708 --> 14:11.379
You're gonna be outta here
in a couple of days, aren't ya?
That's what Dr. Morrison thinks.

14:11.445 --> 14:14.015
I gotta see him
and Dr. Westphall
first thing tomorrow.

14:14.081 --> 14:16.651
Excuse me.
Listen, Miss.
Come here.

14:16.717 --> 14:19.153
What's he doin' in here?
He's a patient.

14:19.220 --> 14:22.657
What does it look like?
I don't want him
in the same room with my son.

14:22.723 --> 14:24.659
I don't handle that, sir.

14:24.725 --> 14:27.161
I suggest you take it up
with Admissions. Excuse me.

14:27.228 --> 14:29.163
<i>Dad-- Come on, Dad.
Don't make trouble.</i>

14:29.230 --> 14:32.767
Hey, I'm not making trouble.
They are.

14:32.833 --> 14:35.002
Dad, look,
he's just a little kid,
for Pete's sake.

14:35.069 --> 14:37.004
Oh, yeah?
The problem is they get bigger.

14:37.071 --> 14:39.006
The only Good thing
that come out of this--

14:39.073 --> 14:41.809
You got some white people
willing to stand up and Fight.
Please, Dad.

14:41.876 --> 14:44.378
I'm going to admissions
and straighten this out.

14:45.413 --> 14:48.149
Dad's a real trip,
isn't he?

14:48.215 --> 14:51.852
We gotta tell, Mike.
I'm not gonna tell nothin'.

14:51.919 --> 14:56.424
don't you see what's happening?
Everybody's beatin'
everybody up because of me.

14:56.490 --> 14:58.626
I'm getting scared here, Mike.
We gotta tell.

14:58.693 --> 15:01.128
You keep your mouth
shut, Kevin.
[ sighs ]

15:06.934 --> 15:09.770
no hockey, huh?
Absolutely not.

15:09.837 --> 15:11.772
He's a tough kid, doc.

15:11.839 --> 15:13.874
Mr. O'Connor, it's not
a question of tough.

15:13.941 --> 15:17.178
He's lost a kidney.
[ sighs ]

15:17.245 --> 15:19.747
sometimes when I work,
the boys help me laying bricks.

15:19.814 --> 15:22.683
<i>Is that out too?
I'd be very, very careful.</i>

15:22.750 --> 15:27.188
Kevin's a good kid.
He's not afraid of work.
Neither one of my boys are.

15:27.255 --> 15:29.390
A couple years ago,
I got a job from the city--
a small one--

15:29.457 --> 15:32.026
to build a park house
down on an empty lot
near Granger and bird.

15:32.093 --> 15:34.862
You know southie?
Not too well.

15:34.929 --> 15:37.298
A couple of days
into the job,
my shoulder went out.

15:37.365 --> 15:41.002
Kevin and Mike carried me.
They finished the job. That's
the kind of kids they are.

15:41.068 --> 15:44.238
Damn Good work too.
Till the niggers got ahold of it
and graffitied it all up.

15:44.305 --> 15:46.607
Now it looks like a--

15:46.674 --> 15:49.243
Well, okay, Doc.
Whatever you say.

15:49.310 --> 15:52.079
Come on down
to southie sometime.
Take you to a couple bars.

15:52.146 --> 15:54.282
Both of you.
We got some nice places
down there.

15:54.348 --> 15:57.885
Mr. O'Connor,
I'd really appreciate it...

15:57.952 --> 16:00.121
if you wouldn't use
the word "Nigger" Around me.

16:00.187 --> 16:02.323
Okay.

16:06.027 --> 16:08.362
All right, Myra. Myra, look,
I'll take care of it.

16:08.429 --> 16:12.233
You're wrong, Wendy.
I'm not. It is starve a cold,
feed a fever.

16:12.300 --> 16:14.635
Why would you want
to feed a fever?
Food is Calories.

16:14.702 --> 16:17.471
Calories is Energy.
Energy is Heat.

16:17.538 --> 16:19.473
Ergo, all you're adding
is fuel to the furnace.

16:19.540 --> 16:21.609
That's right.
Wendy, can I talk to you?

16:21.676 --> 16:23.811
In a minute.
Listen, food is nutrition.

16:23.878 --> 16:26.514
The body needs nutrition
In order to replenish
the immune system.

16:26.581 --> 16:30.084
And that is how
you break a fever.
What do you think, Herb?

16:30.151 --> 16:32.653
Would you go with me
to Craig's party tonight?

16:32.720 --> 16:35.022
Frankly, I don't think
I'm your type.

16:35.089 --> 16:37.058
Me neither.
Come on. Just this once.

16:37.124 --> 16:39.560
I'll leave early.
It'll be short and Painless.

16:39.627 --> 16:41.562
That's why you can
never get a date.

16:41.629 --> 16:44.232
I'm serious here.
If I show up alone
to Craig's party,

16:44.298 --> 16:46.267
he's gonna think
I'm biologically imbalanced.

16:46.334 --> 16:48.803
I've asked everyone.
You're my last hope.

16:48.869 --> 16:51.372
Thanks. I feel the same way
about you.
That's not what I mean.

16:51.439 --> 16:53.708
Save it.
I was invited too.

16:53.774 --> 16:55.776
And I was looking forward
to meeting Dr. Holstrum.

16:55.843 --> 16:57.778
But suddenly, somebody
flip-Flopped the schedule,

16:57.845 --> 17:00.681
and I have to be on duty
for the next 48 hours.

17:00.748 --> 17:02.683
I don't believe this.

17:02.750 --> 17:05.219
I'm going to the cafeteria.
I'm starved.

17:05.286 --> 17:09.624
You got a cold?
Fever. It's a fever.

17:12.359 --> 17:14.462
What am I gonna do?

17:14.528 --> 17:17.565
Let me see
if I have this straight.

17:17.632 --> 17:20.534
You're looking for
a relatively attractive woman,

17:20.601 --> 17:23.237
someone preferably
in the medical profession--
Yes.

17:23.304 --> 17:27.208
Probably lonely,
someone who doesn't care
who she's seen with.

17:27.275 --> 17:29.644
Exactly.
I got the perfect girl.

17:36.751 --> 17:39.020
Hi.
Hi, Victor.

17:39.086 --> 17:41.222
Are you busy?
Yeah.

17:41.289 --> 17:43.257
Could you give me a hand?
Sure.

17:43.324 --> 17:45.693
It's in the bag.

17:45.760 --> 17:48.563
In the bag? Oh.

17:48.629 --> 17:51.098
They found parts of this body
in three neatly wrapped,

17:51.165 --> 17:55.403
individually marked packages
at the back of
the Danny's doughnuts.

17:55.469 --> 18:00.374
It's exciting.
Kind of like putting together
a jigsaw puzzle.

18:00.441 --> 18:02.610
I always had trouble with
those when I was a kid.

18:02.677 --> 18:04.912
They never had
all the pieces.

18:04.979 --> 18:08.683
Neither do we.
foot?

18:08.749 --> 18:10.851
No, that's all there is.

18:10.918 --> 18:14.055
Damn!
We're a foot short.

18:14.121 --> 18:16.657
Can we talk over here?

18:16.724 --> 18:19.160
Sure, Victor.

18:19.226 --> 18:21.162
Um, okay, about tonight.

18:21.228 --> 18:23.164
Craig's gonna have
this little shindig,

18:23.231 --> 18:26.867
and I was sort of hoping
that, um-- that we--
you know, that you and I--

18:26.934 --> 18:30.705
are you asking me out?
I know it's short notice.

18:30.771 --> 18:33.341
That's so sweet of you.
But this guy holstrum,

18:33.407 --> 18:35.943
he's like a norse god
to the medical profession,

18:36.010 --> 18:39.780
and he's only gonna be
in Boston a day before he goes
out west to salt lake City.

18:39.847 --> 18:42.984
Scandinavian culture
has always mystified me.

18:43.050 --> 18:45.519
<i>Did you ever see
the seventh Seal?</i>

18:45.586 --> 18:48.222
Uh, that's Bergman, right?
Right.

18:48.289 --> 18:52.660
The scene where death
is leading Bibi and the rest
across the fjord.

18:52.727 --> 18:54.662
No, I never
actually really saw it.

18:54.729 --> 18:57.765
But what do you say?
About what?

18:57.832 --> 19:01.369
Uh, tonight-- Craig,
party, holstrum.

19:01.435 --> 19:03.771
I'd like to, Victor.
Oh, thank you, thank you!

19:03.838 --> 19:07.475
I really appreciate--
You've saved my life.
Fiscus was right. You're great.

19:07.541 --> 19:10.444
But I can't.
Oh, no.

19:11.979 --> 19:14.815
Cops said to give you this.
Oh, wonderful.

19:14.882 --> 19:16.817
I'm glad you're happy.

19:16.884 --> 19:19.320
I gotta get back to work,
Victor.

19:19.387 --> 19:21.722
Okay. Thanks anyway.

19:29.130 --> 19:31.098
The foot?

19:34.368 --> 19:37.705
Oh!
[ Gasps ]

19:37.772 --> 19:39.774
Well, looks pretty good,
Rowena.
Hey!

19:39.840 --> 19:41.776
You didn't tell me
there was gonna be a scar.

19:41.842 --> 19:44.278
It's a little difficult
to operate without leaving one.

19:44.345 --> 19:46.681
What are you, a wise guy?
And watch your hands.

19:46.747 --> 19:48.749
Nobody rides for free.

19:48.816 --> 19:50.751
It's an examination.
Yeah.

19:50.818 --> 19:53.321
I've had guys who wanted
to play doctor before.

19:53.387 --> 19:55.323
Dion Straightened 'em
right out.

19:55.389 --> 19:58.426
Dion? Who's Dion?
My employer.

19:58.492 --> 20:01.896
The tall guy
standing outside the O.R.,
offered to pay me in cash?

20:01.963 --> 20:04.465
Well, Dion isn't real big
on medical insurance.

20:04.532 --> 20:07.802
And when he sees this scar,
he's gonna kill me.

20:07.868 --> 20:11.672
Yeah, well, it could be worse.
You know, a lot of guys
use Staples these days.

20:11.739 --> 20:13.641
Tell me about it.

20:15.543 --> 20:17.478
The, uh,
rest of the sorority?

20:17.545 --> 20:20.281
Will you stop the cute talk?
When am I gettin' outta here?

20:20.348 --> 20:23.150
Uh, you should be off your back
in three or four days.

20:23.217 --> 20:25.319
I doubt it.

20:32.893 --> 20:36.163
Hi.
Eileen, hi.

20:36.230 --> 20:38.499
How are you feeling?
Better.

20:38.566 --> 20:41.402
Great.
Get a chair.
Sit down.

20:41.469 --> 20:43.571
Are you sure it's okay?
Yeah.

20:43.638 --> 20:45.606
Okay.

20:47.842 --> 20:51.112
I stopped by to see you
the other day,
but you were sleeping.

20:51.178 --> 20:54.715
You could've
woken me up.
I didn't wanna do that.

20:57.218 --> 20:59.120
It's good to see you.
You too.

21:01.856 --> 21:04.558
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>

21:04.625 --> 21:10.031
<i>[ woman on P.A. ]
nurse Goodwin to I.C.U.
Nurse Jessie Goodwin to I.C.U.</i>

21:11.332 --> 21:13.401
Have you seen Fiscus?
He's got your present.

21:13.467 --> 21:15.436
Third Floor.
Great!

21:18.673 --> 21:23.611
<i>Dr. Meyers to n.I.C.U.
 Dr. Nila Meyers to n.I.C.U.</i>

21:23.678 --> 21:25.713
Annie--
Nope.

21:28.716 --> 21:32.053
An Irish kid gets Mugged.
His friends retaliate
by beating up a few blacks.

21:32.119 --> 21:34.622
First thing you know,
three high schools are at war.

21:34.689 --> 21:37.491
Come on.
It's just a bunch of kids
blowing off steam.

21:37.558 --> 21:39.527
No, not really.
Coming to work...

21:39.594 --> 21:41.562
on the bus this morning,
I could feel the tension.

21:41.629 --> 21:43.598
This town is ready to explode.

21:43.664 --> 21:46.033
Well, come the end
of my residency,

21:46.100 --> 21:49.403
I'm getting out of Boston
and setting up my practice
in Scarsdale.

21:49.470 --> 21:52.406
- Not me.
- Aren't you gonna stay?

21:52.473 --> 21:55.309
No way. Santa Barbara.
That's the place for me.

21:55.376 --> 21:59.947
If we all just abandon
st. Eligius, the situation
is not gonna get any better.

22:00.014 --> 22:03.417
<i>Come on, Morrison.
We don't make a difference.</i>

22:03.484 --> 22:07.221
All we do is sew them up
and send them right
back out on the street.

22:07.288 --> 22:09.457
- He's right.
We don't change anything.
- I don't know one woman...

22:09.523 --> 22:12.960
on staff who hasn't been
harassed in the hallway or
threatened in the parking lot.

22:13.027 --> 22:16.464
Maybe Fiscus was right when
he used to carry a gun in E.R.

22:16.530 --> 22:20.635
- Come on, Phil.
- You know what happened
to me the other day?

22:20.701 --> 22:23.304
I was going into
the supply room, and these
kids followed me in there...

22:23.371 --> 22:25.673
looking for god knows what.

22:25.740 --> 22:27.808
And I told them to get out,

22:27.875 --> 22:30.745
but they acted as though
I was the one
who didn't belong in there.

22:30.811 --> 22:32.914
I mean, uh, total spades.

22:32.980 --> 22:35.249
You're a first-Class jerk.
You know that?

22:35.316 --> 22:37.652
Oh, hey, I'm-- I'm sorry.

22:37.718 --> 22:39.954
[ mutters ]

22:42.256 --> 22:44.258
I keep forgetting he's black.

22:44.325 --> 22:47.695
<i>[ woman on P.A. ]
maintenance to n.I.C.U.</i>

22:47.762 --> 22:50.097
<i>Maintenance to n.I.C.U.</i>

22:50.164 --> 22:53.067
<i>Jill.
Peter, hi.</i>

22:53.134 --> 22:55.202
Boy, you left the house
in a hurry this morning.

22:55.269 --> 22:58.639
I was afraid of being late
for rounds. Westphall's
been on my case lately.

22:58.706 --> 23:01.075
Maybe I'm just paranoid.
Here, sit down.
I gotta go.

23:01.142 --> 23:03.077
No, no. We missed out
on having lunch together.

23:03.144 --> 23:05.179
We got a few minutes.
Okay.

23:09.984 --> 23:13.754
Last night was incredible.
Oh, Peter. Shh.

23:13.821 --> 23:18.225
No, really. Since I moved in
with you, you've really
been good for me.

23:18.292 --> 23:20.761
I mean, you've been patient
and understanding.

23:20.828 --> 23:23.731
Kind and all that
sort of thing.
Stop.

23:23.798 --> 23:26.901
That's what makes it hard
for me to ask you something.

23:28.769 --> 23:31.505
Never mind.
Aw, don't be silly.

23:31.572 --> 23:33.908
Come on. You know
I'd do anything for you.

23:33.975 --> 23:36.344
Yeah, I know you would.

23:36.410 --> 23:38.813
And you'd do it without
asking any questions,
wouldn't you?

23:38.879 --> 23:40.848
Of course.
Yeah.

23:41.949 --> 23:45.019
So, what is it?
I need $200.

23:45.086 --> 23:47.154
Huh. Uh--

23:47.221 --> 23:50.358
I'll pay you back, honest.
I promise I'll pay you back.
Okay.

23:50.424 --> 23:52.994
Uh, is-Is a check okay?

23:53.060 --> 23:55.630
Mind if I join you?
No.

23:55.696 --> 23:58.432
You wouldn't believe what just
happened down in Emergency.

23:58.499 --> 24:01.302
This guy comes in unconscious,
every bone in his body broken,

24:01.369 --> 24:04.305
and his pockets are stuffed
with hundred-Dollar bills.

24:04.372 --> 24:08.709
We don't have a c.P.A.
Down there. It took us over
an hour just to count it.

24:08.776 --> 24:12.780
Then he comes to and starts
screaming, "I gotta get
outta here! They're after me!"

24:12.847 --> 24:16.250
next thing we know, he gets
into a private ambulance,
and he's Gone.

24:16.317 --> 24:19.453
Must've been a drug deal.
Crazy, huh?

24:19.520 --> 24:22.290
And then my hair turned green
and the world ended.

24:22.356 --> 24:26.260
Mm-Hmm. Yeah.
Yoo-Hoo, Ehrlich.

24:26.327 --> 24:28.629
I'm sorry, Shirley.
I'm somewhere else.

24:28.696 --> 24:30.631
Why so glum?
Someone drown your puppy?

24:30.698 --> 24:33.200
It's t-minus five hours
and counting.

24:33.267 --> 24:35.670
Ah, still haven't
found ms. Right.

24:35.736 --> 24:38.172
At this point,
I'd settle for Ms. Anyone.

24:38.239 --> 24:40.408
How about a nurse?

24:40.474 --> 24:42.410
What, Rosenthal?
She's married.

24:42.476 --> 24:44.912
Ehrlich.

24:44.979 --> 24:46.914
Shirley.

24:46.981 --> 24:50.051
Ask me. Go ahead.

24:50.117 --> 24:51.719
Shirley?
Yes.

24:51.786 --> 24:53.721
Oh, great.
We don't have to stay too long.

24:53.788 --> 24:55.823
I can't anyway.
I gotta be back here
by 9:00.

24:55.890 --> 24:57.825
Perfect. Just enough time
to go in, work the room,

24:57.892 --> 25:00.227
scarf down some Herring,
get outta there.

25:00.294 --> 25:02.863
Pick me up at 5:30.
I can't.
I don't have a car.

25:02.930 --> 25:05.800
Okay, I'll pick you up
at 5:30.
Fantastic.

25:05.866 --> 25:10.204
This is our first date,
so I should warn you in advance:
I'm not easy.

25:13.941 --> 25:17.478
Remember the cue.
At 8:38, I say,
"Victor, I have a headache."

25:17.545 --> 25:21.148
Right.
Why am I so nervous?
[ Exhales forcefully ]

25:21.215 --> 25:23.417
how do I look?
Uncomfortable.

25:23.484 --> 25:26.754
No, you look fine.
[ inhales sharply ]

25:26.821 --> 25:28.923
remember, 8:38.

25:31.092 --> 25:34.495
Let's make that 7:38.
May I take
your coats, please?

25:34.562 --> 25:39.133
Thank you.
You're welcome.

25:39.200 --> 25:42.169
Hello.
[ Both ]
Hi.

25:42.236 --> 25:44.538
This is Shirley Daniels.
Nice to meet you,
mrs. Craig.

25:44.605 --> 25:46.540
How do you do?
I'm Victor Ehrlich.

25:46.607 --> 25:48.542
Oh, you're the one.
[ laughing ]

25:48.609 --> 25:50.578
I am?

25:50.645 --> 25:53.247
As you can see, you're one of
the first to arrive.

25:53.314 --> 25:56.317
Dr. Craig said
to be here at 6:15 sharp.

25:56.384 --> 25:59.153
Yes. He called from the Airport.

25:59.220 --> 26:03.958
Dr. Holstrum's plane was
rerouted through keflavik
and was late coming in.

26:04.025 --> 26:06.460
Oh, no.
They should be here
any minute.

26:06.527 --> 26:09.130
Make yourselves at home.
I have to check
on the hors D'oeuvres.

26:09.196 --> 26:12.033
Thanks.

26:13.568 --> 26:16.170
Wow. Huh?

26:16.237 --> 26:18.172
Hi. What do you want
to drink?

26:18.239 --> 26:21.175
Um, white wine.
White wine
and a scotch, please.

26:23.210 --> 26:28.749
<i>What a great house. Whoo!
Is this a great house or what?</i>

26:28.816 --> 26:31.586
Avoid that malpractice suit,
and someday all this
will be yours.

26:31.652 --> 26:35.389
Mmm. This is great.

26:35.456 --> 26:37.425
Just great.

26:38.826 --> 26:40.795
Hi.
Hello.

26:44.699 --> 26:46.667
I hate this.

26:49.437 --> 26:53.307
