What?

30:55.116 --> 30:57.151
Yeah. If I had a dollar
for every time...

30:57.218 --> 30:59.553
you dillydallied
in the on-Call room,

30:59.620 --> 31:02.056
I could have
all of those women.

31:02.123 --> 31:04.458
It's your birthday.
Yeah, right.

31:04.525 --> 31:06.594
Last year all you wanted
was celtic tickets.

31:06.661 --> 31:09.564
Well, I'm older now.
Okay, okay.

31:09.630 --> 31:11.599
Thanks! Will you keep
a lookout for me?

31:11.666 --> 31:13.734
Yeah.
One in red.

31:13.801 --> 31:16.270
Okay.

31:16.337 --> 31:21.342
<i>[ woman on P.A. ]
Dr. Steven Nathan, 113.
Dr. Steven Nathan, 113.</i>

31:21.409 --> 31:23.978
<i>[ woman ]
Oh. Hey.</i>

31:24.045 --> 31:26.047
Save me a piece.

31:26.113 --> 31:28.215
<i>[ women chuckling ]
Sure.</i>

31:28.282 --> 31:31.419
Let me get this straight.
With a patient
inside the ambulance?

31:31.485 --> 31:34.855
Yeah. Kemler's driving
the ambulance round
and round the hospital,

31:34.922 --> 31:38.626
full speed, siren blasting,
drunk as a Skunk.

31:38.693 --> 31:41.028
Think the Patient'll Sue?
Wouldn't you?

31:43.998 --> 31:46.968
Dr. Cavanero,
I see you're working the halls
like everyone else.

31:47.034 --> 31:51.005
Uh-Huh.
Don't get caught
under any red lights.

31:51.072 --> 31:54.175
I can't believe you ran out
of the little hot dogs
wrapped in Bacon.

31:54.242 --> 31:57.245
Mark, this is a cocktail party,
not the last supper.

31:57.311 --> 32:00.581
So I said to Borg--
I said, "bjorn,
use your backstroke."

32:00.648 --> 32:04.385
Ooh, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, sven.
You mind if I call you sven?

32:04.452 --> 32:06.721
Fiscus--
All right.

32:06.787 --> 32:08.956
Luther's having a private
birthday Celebration.

32:09.023 --> 32:12.660
<i>Hats, cake, party favors.
[ Luther ]
wow!</i>

32:12.727 --> 32:17.698
[ chuckles ]
I guess he just had
his candles blown out.

32:22.003 --> 32:24.005
What time is it?
7:40.

32:24.071 --> 32:26.340
- I have a headache, Victor.
- So what?

32:26.407 --> 32:29.944
It's a migraine!

32:30.011 --> 32:34.448
Listen, sven, do you mind if I
get very personal with you
for just one second?

32:34.515 --> 32:36.584
Could you get me a deal
on a new saab?
[ laughing ]

32:36.651 --> 32:39.253
Oh, for crying out loud.

32:39.320 --> 32:41.255
[ laughing Continues ]

32:41.322 --> 32:46.260
uh, Dr. Holstrum,
there's someone
I would like you to meet.

32:46.327 --> 32:48.296
Oh.

32:49.330 --> 32:51.732
Great party, mark.

32:51.799 --> 32:54.669
[ Clears throat ]

32:54.735 --> 32:57.772
I think he's mad.
Victor, I really think you
should slow down on the scotch.

32:57.838 --> 33:00.007
Okay, take it easy.
I'll sip the next one.

33:00.074 --> 33:02.009
I don't know about you,
but I'm out of here.

33:02.076 --> 33:04.412
Me too. Can you give me
a lift to the hospital?
Sure.

33:04.478 --> 33:06.981
Don't be party poopers.
You're gonna hurt
Sven's feelings.

33:07.048 --> 33:10.084
Sven's from Scandinavia.
He doesn't have feelings.

33:10.151 --> 33:12.753
Besides, they ran out of
those little hot dogs
wrapped in Bacon.

33:12.820 --> 33:15.456
You're kidding.
You really think
we should leave him here?

33:15.523 --> 33:18.526
He couldn't possibly do
any more damage
than he's already done.

33:19.760 --> 33:22.830
I'll have a double
of anything, please.

33:22.897 --> 33:24.799
Hi.
Hi.

33:29.537 --> 33:31.839
<i>[ woman ]
my baby!</i>

33:33.741 --> 33:35.743
Make way for the crash cart.

33:35.810 --> 33:39.981
<i>- [ chattering ]
- My baby!</i>

33:40.047 --> 33:44.118
<i>My baby! My baby!
[ Sobbing ]</i>

33:51.626 --> 33:54.662
<i>[ man ]
Good. Okay.
Try to stabilize him now.</i>

34:01.469 --> 34:03.437
Ooh, you're tight.

34:04.739 --> 34:06.707
That's o--
Don't, please.

34:08.175 --> 34:10.811
What's the matter?
Nothing.

34:10.878 --> 34:12.847
Nothing?
Yeah.

34:14.782 --> 34:16.751
Mmm.

34:18.185 --> 34:21.054
Don't, please.
[ Clears Throat ]

34:21.121 --> 34:23.123
is something wrong?
No, Nothing's wrong.

34:23.190 --> 34:26.226
I just, uh--
Just want to go to sleep.

34:27.962 --> 34:29.897
You said it was great.

34:29.964 --> 34:32.500
It is. But we don't have to
every night.

34:33.601 --> 34:36.536
Well, okay.
But I read in an article--

34:36.603 --> 34:39.540
<i>I think it was in cosmo--
That, uh,</i>

34:39.607 --> 34:45.012
the lack of Regular sex
is the first sign
of a failing relationship.

34:46.112 --> 34:48.649
Do you believe
everything you read?

34:48.716 --> 34:50.650
One lousy night
I don't want to make love
to you,

34:50.717 --> 34:52.954
and you're giving me all
this grief about our sex life.

34:53.020 --> 34:56.857
I was only kidding, Peter.
No. I get up early,
I put in a full day.

34:56.924 --> 35:00.294
I don't have to
explain myself to you.
Okay, I'm sorry.

35:00.361 --> 35:02.296
Uh, I'm gonna go
watch some tv.

35:02.363 --> 35:04.432
No.

35:04.498 --> 35:06.834
I'm sorry.

35:06.901 --> 35:08.869
Okay.

35:13.140 --> 35:16.444
Okay. I got sven settled in
at the Ritz.

35:18.512 --> 35:20.781
All in all, I'd say
the party was a triumph.

35:20.848 --> 35:22.783
You think so?
Oh, yeah.

35:22.850 --> 35:24.952
Follow me.

35:25.019 --> 35:26.988
What?
Over here.

35:30.558 --> 35:32.960
He just threw up
in the gladiolas.

35:33.027 --> 35:35.196
Oh, my God.
He's all yours.

35:35.263 --> 35:38.900
I'm going to bed.
[ Stammering ]
Ellen, wait--

35:38.966 --> 35:40.935
Okay, Ehrlich.

35:42.904 --> 35:45.806
<i>Up and at 'em.
Valkommen, valkommen, Valkommen.</i>

35:45.873 --> 35:49.410
Yeah, yeah, sure.
The Party's over, pal.

35:49.477 --> 35:52.046
Here, sit.
Oh, Dr. Craig, I'm sorry.

35:52.113 --> 35:54.081
We gotta go.
She's got a headache.

35:54.148 --> 35:56.384
I'm gonna get your coat.
You're gonna go home.

35:56.450 --> 35:58.886
Oh, what have I done?

36:09.597 --> 36:11.966
Pathetic, Ehrlich.

36:15.469 --> 36:18.773
He's in the bathroom crying.
He's got a razor in his hand.

36:18.839 --> 36:20.841
Did he hurt himself?
No, not that I know of.

36:20.908 --> 36:24.645
He better not cut hisself.
It's gonna be me
that has to clean it up.

36:24.712 --> 36:28.182
Oh! Is somebody with him?
The nurse is in there.

36:32.420 --> 36:36.123
Thank you.
[ crying ]

36:44.832 --> 36:46.801
I couldn't do it.

36:51.639 --> 36:53.741
Why would you want to?

36:55.076 --> 36:58.246
Because of everything
that's happened.

36:58.312 --> 37:01.816
That boy that died.
Everything's all my fault.

37:01.882 --> 37:05.453
What happened to you
has absolutely nothing to do
with That boy dying.

37:05.519 --> 37:09.290
It's all a lie!
It's my father that beat me up!

37:09.357 --> 37:11.459
[ Sobbing ]

37:14.762 --> 37:20.067
<i>[ Craig ]
I don't understand what
went wrong with this town.</i>

37:20.134 --> 37:24.071
<i>They spend millions of my
tax dollars, and the schools
are still toilets.</i>

37:24.138 --> 37:26.874
Croissant, Victor?
No, um--

37:26.941 --> 37:29.243
Okay, maybe I'll
just have one.
Okay.

37:29.310 --> 37:31.712
I wish I could give you
something for your headache.

37:31.779 --> 37:34.115
I'm okay.
You want some jam?

37:34.181 --> 37:36.851
Um, no.
No, I'm fine, thank you.

37:36.918 --> 37:38.853
These kids are not interested
in an education.

37:38.920 --> 37:41.355
They're interested
in a good time.

37:41.422 --> 37:44.725
They don't understand
that good times
are the result of hard work.

37:44.792 --> 37:47.895
<i>- Am I right, Ellen?
- Yes, dear.</i>

37:47.962 --> 37:50.197
Coffee?
Please.

37:52.433 --> 37:54.702
Victor?

37:54.769 --> 37:57.672
No, thank you.
That's fine.

37:58.706 --> 38:00.908
It gives all of Boston
a black eye.

38:00.975 --> 38:03.444
Dr. Craig,
about last night.

38:03.511 --> 38:06.047
What about it?

38:06.113 --> 38:08.182
I can't tell you
how badly I feel.

38:08.249 --> 38:11.052
Emotionally or physically?

38:11.118 --> 38:14.422
Both. I-I-I-- I really
don't know what happened.

38:14.488 --> 38:17.024
Well, I'll tell you
what happened.
You got blind Drunk.

38:17.091 --> 38:19.060
That's what happened.

38:19.126 --> 38:22.530
I know, and I just wanted
to apologize to both of you.

38:22.597 --> 38:25.366
It's all right.
Don't worry.
Everything's fine.

38:25.433 --> 38:27.468
No, it's not.

38:27.535 --> 38:30.605
I mean, sven holstrum
came all the way over here
from oslo--

38:30.671 --> 38:34.075
Stockholm.
Well, wherever the hell
he came from.

38:34.141 --> 38:38.079
- You're supposed to be
apologizing to him.
- I will.

38:38.145 --> 38:40.081
How do you say "I'm sorry"
in swedish?

38:40.147 --> 38:43.317
I went to a lot of trouble,
Ehrlich, and you let me down.

38:43.384 --> 38:46.921
<i>Now, I can understand you being
nervous or uncomfortable.</i>

38:46.988 --> 38:49.924
And I've been known
to hoist a few in my time.

38:49.991 --> 38:55.229
But what disappoints me the most
is that you are on call today,

38:55.296 --> 38:57.465
and I don't think you're capable
of doing the work.

38:57.531 --> 39:01.869
- But I am.
- Your responsibility is to
your patients, damn it!

39:03.304 --> 39:05.673
<i>Twenty-Four hours a day.</i>

39:07.308 --> 39:10.912
I thought you
were the brightest.
I thought you were the best.

39:13.514 --> 39:16.017
Now I'm not so sure anymore.

39:16.083 --> 39:19.453
I'll be down in five minutes.
I'll drive you to the hospital.

39:22.423 --> 39:25.493
Just ignore him, Victor.
That's what I do.

39:26.594 --> 39:28.563
I feel terrible.

39:29.830 --> 39:31.933
I mean, I really feel Terrible
about everything.

39:31.999 --> 39:34.936
<i>[ woman on P.A. ]
code Blue. Code Blue.</i>

39:35.002 --> 39:37.505
We never even got started.
I took off my pants.

39:37.572 --> 39:39.574
Before you knew it,
he stopped breathing.

39:39.640 --> 39:42.276
Okay, fine.
Go wait down the Hall.

39:42.343 --> 39:45.212
That's it.
You've got to put
an end to this.

39:45.279 --> 39:47.448
You should have brought it
to my attention sooner.

39:47.515 --> 39:51.152
I didn't think I needed to.
They're like rabbits.

39:51.218 --> 39:54.355
First there were two,
then there were six,
and now they're everywhere.

39:54.422 --> 39:56.624
And it's not just
the patients, Daniel.

39:56.691 --> 39:59.794
Male members of my staff
keep disappearing
for hours at a time.

39:59.860 --> 40:02.263
Perhaps we ought to have
a meeting with the ladies.

40:02.330 --> 40:04.265
A meeting?

40:04.332 --> 40:06.500
Daniel,
these aren't quakers.

40:06.567 --> 40:11.339
Helen, it's essential
in matters of this kind
to be diplomatic.

40:15.243 --> 40:20.381
Well, see, me and my Brother
were going to
st. Margaret's,

40:20.448 --> 40:22.783
a catholic school.

40:22.850 --> 40:24.885
And then the old man
got laid off,

40:24.952 --> 40:28.055
so we've been going to
this public high school
in southie.

40:28.122 --> 40:30.491
<i>And I like it there.</i>

40:30.558 --> 40:34.262
Anyway, Eileen--
That's my friend.

40:34.328 --> 40:37.798
Well, we were in
the same classes together.

40:37.865 --> 40:41.602
And, see, she lives in roxbury,
but they bus her in.

40:41.669 --> 40:44.538
And I knew my dad
wouldn't like it.

40:44.605 --> 40:48.609
<i>But we started
spending time together,
and we became friends.</i>

40:48.676 --> 40:52.413
You know, like you do
when you see somebody
in school every day, and--

40:53.481 --> 40:55.650
So I told my brother
Mike about it.

40:55.716 --> 40:59.420
You know, about me
being friends with Eileen,

40:59.487 --> 41:02.957
and... then he told Dad.

41:03.024 --> 41:05.359
<i>Mike didn't know
he was gonna beat me.</i>

41:05.426 --> 41:08.095
Your father beat you 'cause you
were friends with a black girl?

41:08.162 --> 41:11.098
No, he thought it
was more than that.

41:11.165 --> 41:13.935
Kevin, what we're gonna do is...

41:14.001 --> 41:16.370
get ahold of social services
and find you a place to stay.

41:16.437 --> 41:18.906
- No.
- You can't go home
with that man again.

41:18.973 --> 41:21.409
We'll call the police
so you can press charges.

41:21.475 --> 41:23.978
I can't do that!
He's my father!

41:24.045 --> 41:26.647
Kevin, he could do it again!

41:26.714 --> 41:30.418
- Next time, I'll run.
- Next time, he could blind you.

41:30.484 --> 41:33.988
- He's my father.
- He almost killed you, son.

41:34.055 --> 41:39.794
Look, I know one thing
for sure, and that's that he
loves me and my brother.

41:39.860 --> 41:41.729
He needs us.

41:50.638 --> 41:53.407
What can we do?

41:53.474 --> 41:55.977
He's too old to be
a ward of the state,
and he won't press charges.

41:56.043 --> 41:58.312
[ sighs ]

41:58.379 --> 42:01.415
- So that's it?
- [ clicks tongue ]
Maybe.

42:03.184 --> 42:05.052
<i>[ women chattering ]</i>

42:17.431 --> 42:21.402
- Ladies--
- Hey, doc,
you want a cheeseburger?

42:21.469 --> 42:24.972
No, thank you.
I've already eaten.

42:25.039 --> 42:30.344
Ladies, I'm afraid I'll have to
ask all of you to leave these
hospital grounds immediately.

42:30.411 --> 42:33.781
- Why? It's still
visiting hours.
- Visiting hours is one thing.

42:33.848 --> 42:38.452
Soliciting is another.
Helen, please,
let me handle this.

42:38.519 --> 42:41.355
Ladies, you're a distraction,
albeit a pleasant one.

42:41.422 --> 42:45.559
<i>And I'm afraid
you're disrupting the day-To-Day
functioning of this institution.</i>

42:45.626 --> 42:49.130
- All we're doing
is making a living.
- Not in here, you're--

42:49.196 --> 42:52.600
Helen, please.
[ Clears throat ]

42:52.667 --> 42:56.003
now, I don't support
restraint of trade--

42:57.838 --> 43:00.174
How shall I phrase this?

43:00.241 --> 43:06.013
When a plumber comes to visit
a sick coworker here,

43:06.080 --> 43:09.050
he doesn't go around
unclogging all our sinks.

43:09.116 --> 43:11.552
You must learn
to curb your activities.

43:11.619 --> 43:15.022
It's not up to us, man.
It's up to Dion.

43:15.089 --> 43:17.325
<i>He calls the shots.
Who's Dion?</i>

43:20.161 --> 43:23.564
Oh, to hell with Diplomacy.

43:23.631 --> 43:28.369
Listen, Dion, personally,
I think what you're doing
to these women stinks.

43:28.436 --> 43:30.471
But that's not the issue.

43:30.538 --> 43:33.374
What we're trying to run here,
Buster, is a hospital.

43:33.441 --> 43:38.346
Now, that is difficult enough
without this kind of aberrant
behavior infesting the hallways.

43:38.412 --> 43:42.250
So, either you get them out of
here in the next five minutes,

43:42.316 --> 43:45.019
<i>or you'll be given a personal
escort from the Boston police
vice squad,</i>

43:45.086 --> 43:47.622
who, I might add, are already
on their way!

43:47.688 --> 43:49.890
Eloquently put, Helen.

43:55.863 --> 43:59.433
You got one hell of a nerve
sticking your face in people's
business-- Family business!

43:59.500 --> 44:04.205
You beat up your son.
What goes on between me and my
boys is no concern of yours!

44:04.272 --> 44:07.275
You smashed his nose,
you broke his ribs.
He lost a kidney.

44:07.341 --> 44:09.944
You're lucky he didn't die.
I know what
you're trying to do.

44:10.011 --> 44:12.079
You doctors think you're
better than people like me.

44:12.146 --> 44:15.316
Let me tell you something.
I love my boys.
What we got you can't touch.

44:15.383 --> 44:17.318
I've been a good father to them
since their mother died.

44:17.385 --> 44:20.788
Ain't been a day gone by
that they ain't had clean
clothes and a decent meal.

44:20.855 --> 44:22.924
I grew up with people
like you, O'Connor.

44:22.990 --> 44:25.059
I know how tough
it's been for you.

44:25.126 --> 44:30.031
But you're not the only one
in this world that ever
lost a job or a wife.

44:30.097 --> 44:32.033
You talk about love
and family and respect.

44:32.099 --> 44:34.802
You don't even know
what those words mean.
All you know is you're angry.

44:34.869 --> 44:37.305
You have to hit people.
And the sickest part
of it is...

44:37.371 --> 44:39.974
you take it out on the people
you supposedly care
the most about.

44:40.041 --> 44:43.711
Shove that
dime-Store shrink talk!
I hate people like you!

44:43.778 --> 44:45.713
And I'm telling you
something right now.

44:45.780 --> 44:49.350
I'm gonna do everything in my
power to stop you from doing
any more damage to that boy.

44:49.417 --> 44:53.120
Why, you--
You gonna swing on me?
You wanna hit me?

44:53.187 --> 44:56.490
Wouldn't you feel a little
more comfortable with
a baseball bat in your hand?

44:56.557 --> 44:58.593
I learned to fight
the same place you did,
pally-Boy.

44:58.659 --> 45:01.228
There's nothing
I'd like better right now
than to tear you apart.

45:14.909 --> 45:18.312
The thing that keeps
coming back to me is
how much trouble this caused...

45:18.379 --> 45:21.649
and how quick everybody
was to accept a lie.

45:21.716 --> 45:24.418
Yeah, well,
that's Boston for you.

45:24.485 --> 45:26.520
Everybody's image
is of Bunker hill,

45:26.587 --> 45:30.124
crew races on
the Charles river, M.I.T.

45:30.191 --> 45:32.960
The reality is
that walking in Boston's
historic Freedom Trail...

45:33.027 --> 45:35.796
is more dangerous than walking
in a freedom March down South.

45:35.863 --> 45:38.432
Yeah, I'm beginning
to agree with you.

45:40.968 --> 45:43.104
<i>I don't know.</i>

45:43.170 --> 45:47.508
I guess I never had to be
concerned with the big
issues of race relations.

45:47.575 --> 45:50.144
I always dealt
with people one-On-One.

45:50.211 --> 45:52.647
I mean, we're friends,
aren't we?

45:54.982 --> 45:57.451
Aren't we?

45:57.518 --> 46:02.256
Jack, I'd like to say, "Yeah,
sure. We're friends. No problem.
Everything's fine."

46:02.323 --> 46:05.192
But I can't.

46:05.259 --> 46:08.195
There's things about me
you'll never understand
because you're white.

46:08.262 --> 46:10.197
I'm not trying
to pass judgment.

46:10.264 --> 46:13.768
There's things about your wife
you'll never understand
because she's a woman.

46:13.834 --> 46:17.805
Yeah. But she's still my wife,
and we're still friends.

46:25.346 --> 46:27.281
I'm sorry about
what Kiley said today.

46:27.348 --> 46:29.584
<i>You don't have to apologize
for Dr. Kiley, all right?</i>

46:29.650 --> 46:32.887
<i>You're not responsible
for Dr. Kiley.
I know, but he was wrong.</i>

46:32.954 --> 46:36.924
I'm on the bus yesterday.
My beeper goes off.

46:36.991 --> 46:39.527
There's a couple of brothers
there about our age.

46:39.594 --> 46:41.996
Started giving me a hard time.

46:42.063 --> 46:46.834
Said, "look at this uptown
nigger with his
beacon hill clothes,

46:46.901 --> 46:49.637
Bourgeois attitude."

46:49.704 --> 46:53.007
So I told 'em to lay off,
all right? I'm a doctor.

46:53.074 --> 46:55.710
Funniest Thing
they ever heard.

46:55.776 --> 47:00.214
One guy even says,
"Yeah, I'm gonna be president
one day, bro."

47:00.281 --> 47:04.051
and I'm standing there
trying to apologize to them
like I did something wrong.

47:04.118 --> 47:09.223
I mean, it's--
I can't be responsible
for everybody, Jack.

47:11.525 --> 47:13.494
Want a ride home?

47:15.930 --> 47:19.600
You sure you want to ride
into my neighborhood?
Yeah, I'll take my chances.

47:19.667 --> 47:22.470
Seeing as you only live
two Blocks from me.

47:28.676 --> 47:30.645
I'll catch you outside, Jack.

47:35.116 --> 47:38.085
<i>[ people chattering ]</i>

48:53.527 --> 48:54.762
[ mews ]
